node.text: Tiffany Blue® isn’t the only blue we care about. Since its inception in 2000, The Tiffany & Co. Foundation has awarded over $26 million to organizations that support coral and marine conservation in more than 30 countries around the world. In the face of climate change, it is imperative we act now to protect this source of life, food, beauty and recreation. It’s about time we started to make waves. Link in bio for more. #WorldOceansDay #TiffanySustainability

Chef @mvoltaggio and designer and stylist @samimiro take over T Time, our Instagram Live series. Add the below ingredients to your shopping list and follow along with the couple as they put a Tiffany twist on holiday hors d’oeuvres. #TiffanyAndCo  
 
Ingredients: 
4 oz smoked salmon 
¼ cup cream cheese (whipped)
1 bunch of chives (for gold strings)
1 tablespoon of chives (for mix) 
Zest of ½ lemon 
5 eggs 
3 cups milk 
1 cup flour 
1 tablespoon butterfly pea flower powder 
¼ tablespoon caviar (per pouch)
Edible gold luster powder
Salt and black pepper (to taste)

node.text: “I wanted to give the Blue Box this distressed quality to represent how much of a fixture it is in our world today, and how it will continue to be relevant decades, even centuries from now,” says artist @danielarsham. Discover his entire limited-run immersive installation at The Tiffany Flagship Next Door in NYC, now through October. Link in bio. #TiffanyKnot #TiffanyAndCo

node.text: The limited-edition @danielarsham Tiffany Knot bracelet features hand-set tsavorites that hint at both his studio color and the patina of his Bronze Eroded Tiffany Blue Box®. Link in bio. #TiffanyKnot #TiffanyAndCo

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tiffany & Co. on September 08, 2021.

node.text: “When I visited The Tiffany Archive, it felt very much of my world. I am deeply familiar with the materials, the techniques, the innovations that are on full display there,” says @danielarsham. “Bronze casting, metal chasing—it’s a craft I know well. When you see some of the works there and the level of detail that went into those pieces, the drawings; it’s fascinating.” Pictured here, an original Blue Box from the Tiffany Archive that served as inspiration for the collaboration. Link in bio. #TiffanyKnot #TiffanyAndCo

node.text: Inside the @danielarsham Tiffany Blue Box® sculpture is a limited-edition Tiffany Knot bracelet. The exclusive 18k white gold bracelet is hand-set with diamonds and tsavorites—the vivid green Tiffany legacy gemstone that we proudly introduced to the world in 1974. Link in bio. #TiffanyKnot #TiffanyAndCo

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tiffany & Co. on September 07, 2021.

node.text: Artist @danielarsham transforms our iconic packaging into a work of sculptural distortion. Rendering the familiar into something altogether new, he bridges past, present and future with his Bronze Eroded Tiffany Blue Box®. The result?
